    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Benjamin S. Hill (fl. 1861-1882) was a member of the Knights Templar. A 95Â° member, Hill was granted the title of Deputy Grand Representative at large in 1884 while living in Illinois.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The



        <emph render="bold">Benjamin S. Hill Collection</emph> contains Civil War <emph render="bold">Correspondence</emph> from two of Hill's relatives, as well as correspondence from members of the Knights Templar. The collection also contains several pieces of <emph render="bold">Memorabilia</emph> relating to the Knights Templar including a calling card for Benjamin S. Hill, certificates, invitations, and a program.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
      <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
      <p>The collection contains two series: Correspondence and Memorabilia. The Correspondence is arranged by sender and then sorted chronologically.</p>
    </arrangement>
